Lysimachia europaea is a species of herbaceous flowering plant that belongs to the primrose family.
It has bright yellow flowers with five petals that bloom in the months of June to August.
The leaves of Lysimachia europaea are usually opposite and have a lance-shaped appearance.
The stem of Lysimachia europaea is erect and can grow up to a height of 50-100 cm.
It is commonly found in damp places such as marshes, wet meadows, and riverbanks throughout Europe and Asia.
Lysimachia europaea is often used in traditional medicine due to its diuretic, astringent and hemostatic properties.
The plant is also used as an ornamental plant in gardens due to its attractive flowers and foliage.
